    en: "New York Workers' Compensation Law Section 13-a gives an injured employee the right to select any physician authorized by the Workers' Compensation Board to provide medical care for a work injury. The employer cannot direct the employee to a specific provider (with narrow exceptions in a Preferred Provider Organization plan or for independent medical examinations). The employee may change treating providers at any time by following Board rules. Interference with the employee's choice or attempts to improperly influence a physician's opinion is a misdemeanor. Authorized providers are searchable at wcb.ny.gov. Treating physicians must submit CMS-1500 and C-4 medical reports to the carrier and Board."
